{"overview":"This piece is a brooding ballad in D minor cast in a large ternary form, characterized by a solemn hymn-like primary theme evoking Scottish folk tradition and an exceptionally adventurous harmonic journey through the middle section that traverses D major, B minor, and F# major via sequential third-relations and an enharmonic return. Its most distinctive feature is the bold enharmonic modulation at bar 45 that snaps the listener back from the remote brightness of F# major into the dark gravity of D minor, lending the recapitulation a sense of inevitable tragic return.","cross_piece_tags":["ballade","ternary","modal_mixture","enharmonic_modulation","chromatic_mediant","circle_of_fifths","arpeggiated_bass","melancholic","tragic","lyrical","meditative"]}
